  "time_ut": 1660985765,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dc0\u0dd4\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dd4 2\u0da7 \u0d85\u0da9\u0dd4 \u0daf\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0db1 \u0db8\u0dc0\u0dca\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0daf\u0dd9\u0dc3\u0dca\u0d9c\u0dad\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db8\u0da7 \u0d85\u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb \u0db1\u0dd1",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Mothers with children under 2 years old are not allowed to go abroad",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is mandatory for women who go abroad for work to confirm through an affidavit that they have made arrangements for the protection of their minor children when registering with the Sri Lanka Foreign Employment Bureau. The Ministry of Labor and Foreign Employment has issued a new circular in this regard. This circular has been issued as per the decision taken in the Cabinet meeting held on 27.06.2022.",
        "This new amendment does not allow mothers with children under 2 years of age to go for foreign employment, and such women do not have the opportunity to register with the Sri Lanka Foreign Employment Bureau.",
        "Also, when women going abroad for work get registered with the Sri Lanka Foreign Employment Bureau, they have/don't have children or mothers with unmarried children above two years of age and below 18 years of age, an affidavit regarding the measures taken for the safety and education of those children in the domain of their residence. It should be certified by the village officer and given to the concerned Regional Secretariat.",
        "The documents thus completed should be verified by the Development Officer (Foreign Employment) attached to the Regional Secretary's office and the information regarding the recommendation or non-recommendation for the travel abroad made by the said officer should be confirmed to the Bureau by SMS. .",
        "Nevertheless, according to the circular presented by the Ministry Secretary, this report covers the women who come to Sri Lanka after having registered with the Bureau for a job and then prepare a re-entry visa, and the women who return to Sri Lanka after registering with the Bureau and going abroad for a job within a period of 6 months. Exempted from delivery.",
        "Also, especially women who have not been registered with the bureau before must get this report, and those who do not have any chance to go abroad for work. The Bureau informs that this program will be implemented from 19.08.2022 according to the new amendment.",
        "In addition to this, women over the age of 45 have been removed from these restrictions, but from 2022.08.19, they must complete the documents required to obtain bureau registration. This process is simply a step taken to successfully carry out the care and education work of the children of the mothers going abroad. Also, identifying the family members who are willing to be responsible for the responsibility of the children during the period of overseas service, and for those families who are identified as needing special intervention/relief from the ministry or office officials. This is expected to implement the plans that have been prepared to provide concessions more efficiently."
      ],
